05872 /**
05873  * cvmx_usbdrd#_uctl_ctl
05874  *
05875  * This register controls clocks, resets, power, and BIST.
05876  *
05877  * This register can be reset by IOI reset.
05878  */
05879 union cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_ctl {
05880     uint64_t u64;
05881     struct cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_ctl_s {
05882 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
05883     uint64_t clear_bist                   : 1;  /**< BIST fast-clear mode select. A BIST run with this bit set clears all entries in USBDRD
05884                                                          RAMs
05885                                                          to 0x0.
05886                                                          There are two major modes of BIST: full and clear. Full BIST is run by the BIST state
05887                                                          machine when CLEAR_BIST is deasserted during BIST. Clear BIST is run if CLEAR_BIST is
05888                                                          asserted during BIST.
05889                                                          To avoid race conditions, software must first perform a CSR write operation that puts the
05890                                                          CLEAR_BIST setting into the correct state and then perform another CSR write operation to
05891                                                          set the BIST trigger (keeping the CLEAR_BIST state constant).
05892                                                          CLEAR BIST completion is indicated by USBDRD()_UCTL_BIST_STATUS. A BIST clear operation
05893                                                          takes almost 2,000 controller-clock cycles for the largest RAM. */
05894     uint64_t start_bist                   : 1;  /**< Rising edge starts BIST on the memories in USBDRD.
05895                                                          To run BIST, the controller clock must be both configured and enabled, and should be
05896                                                          configured to the maximum available frequency given the available coprocessor clock and
05897                                                          dividers.
05898                                                          Also, the UCTL, UAHC, and UPHY should be held in software- initiated reset (using
05899                                                          UPHY_RST, UAHC_RST, UCTL_RST) until BIST is complete.
05900                                                          BIST defect status can be checked after FULL BIST completion, both of which are indicated
05901                                                          in USBDRD()_UCTL_BIST_STATUS. The full BIST run takes almost 80,000 controller-clock
05902                                                          cycles
05903                                                          for
05904                                                          the largest RAM. */
05905     uint64_t ref_clk_sel                  : 2;  /**< Reference clock select. Choose reference-clock source for the SuperSpeed and high-speed
05906                                                          PLL blocks.
05907                                                          0x0 = Reference clock sources for both PLLs come from the USB pads.
05908                                                          0x1 = Reserved.
05909                                                          0x2 = Reserved.
05910                                                          0x3 = Reserved.
05911                                                          This value can be changed only during UPHY_RST.
05912                                                          If REF_CLK_SEL = 0x0, then the reference clock input cannot be spread-spectrum. */
05913     uint64_t ssc_en                       : 1;  /**< Spread-spectrum clock enable. Enables spread-spectrum clock production in the SuperSpeed
05914                                                          function. If the input reference clock for the SuperSpeed PLL is already spread-spectrum,
05915                                                          then do not enable this feature. The clocks sourced to the SuperSpeed function must have
05916                                                          spread-spectrum to be compliant with the USB specification.
05917                                                          The high-speed PLL cannot support a spread-spectrum input, so REF_CLK_SEL = 0x0 must
05918                                                          enable this feature.
05919                                                          This value may only be changed during [UPHY_RST]. */
05920     uint64_t ssc_range                    : 3;  /**< Spread-spectrum clock range. Selects the range of spread-spectrum modulation when SSC_EN
05921                                                          is asserted and the PHY is spreading the SuperSpeed transmit clocks.
05922                                                          Applies a fixed offset to the phase accumulator.
05923                                                          0x0 = -4980 ppm downspread of clock.
05924                                                          0x1 = -4492 ppm.
05925                                                          0x2 = -4003 ppm.
05926                                                          0x3-0x7 = reserved.
05927                                                          All of these settings are within the USB 3.0 specification. The amount of EMI emission
05928                                                          reduction might decrease as the [SSC_RANGE] increases; therefore, the [SSC_RANGE] settings
05929                                                          can
05930                                                          be registered to enable the amount of spreading to be adjusted on a per-application basis.
05931                                                          This value can be changed only during UPHY_RST. */
05932     uint64_t ssc_ref_clk_sel              : 9;  /**< Enables non-standard oscillator frequencies to generate targeted MPLL output rates. Input
05933                                                          corresponds to the frequency-synthesis coefficient.
05934                                                          [55:53]: modulus - 1,
05935                                                          [52:47]: 2's complement push amount
05936                                                          A value of 0x0 means this feature is disabled.
05937                                                          The legal values are:
05938                                                            If REF_CLK_SEL = 0x0 or 0x1, then:
05939                                                              0x0 is the only legal value.
05940                                                            If REF_CLK_SEL = 0x2 or 0x3, then:
05941                                                              0x0:   if DLMC_REF_CLK* is another supported frequency (see list in
05942                                                                     MPLL_MULTIPLIER description).
05943                                                          All other values are reserved.
05944                                                          This value may only be changed during [UPHY_RST].
05945                                                          Note: If REF_CLK_SEL = 0x2 or 0x3, then MPLL_MULTPLIER, REF_CLK_DIV2, and SSC_REF_CLK_SEL
05946                                                          must all be programmed to the same frequency setting. */
05947     uint64_t mpll_multiplier              : 7;  /**< Multiplies the reference clock to a frequency suitable for intended operating speed. The
05948                                                          legal values are:
05949                                                            If REF_CLK_SEL = 0x0 or 0x1, then:
05950                                                              0x19 = 100  MHz on DLMC_REF_CLK*
05951                                                            If REF_CLK_SEL = 0x2 or 0x3, then:
05952                                                              0x32 =  50  MHz on DLMC_REF_CLK*
05953                                                              0x19 =  100 MHz on DLMC_REF_CLK*
05954                                                              0x28 =  125 MHz on DLMC_REF_CLK*
05955                                                          All other values are reserved.
05956                                                          This value may only be changed during [UPHY_RST].
05957                                                          Note: If REF_CLK_SEL = 0x2 or 0x3, then MPLL_MULTPLIER, REF_CLK_DIV2, and SSC_REF_CLK_SEL
05958                                                          must all be programmed to the same frequency setting. */
05959     uint64_t ref_ssp_en                   : 1;  /**< Enables reference clock to the prescaler for SuperSpeed function. This should always be
05960                                                          enabled since this output clock is used to drive the UAHC suspend-mode clock during
05961                                                          low-power states.
05962                                                          This value can be changed only during UPHY_RST or during low-power states.
05963                                                          The reference clock must be running and stable before UPHY_RST is deasserted and before
05964                                                          REF_SSP_EN is asserted. */
05965     uint64_t ref_clk_div2                 : 1;  /**< Divides the reference clock by 2 before feeding it into the REF_CLK_FSEL divider.
05966                                                          The legal values are:
05967                                                            If REF_CLK_SEL = 0x0 or 0x1, then:
05968                                                              all DLMC_REF_CLK* frequencies: 0x0 is the only legal value.
05969                                                            If REF_CLK_SEL = 0x2 or 0x3, then:
05970                                                              0x1: if DLMC_REF_CLK* is 125MHz.
05971                                                              0x0: if DLMC_REF_CLK* is another supported frequency (see list in
05972                                                                   MPLL_MULTIPLIER description).
05973                                                          This value can be changed only during UPHY_RST.
05974                                                          Note: If REF_CLK_SEL = 0x2 or 0x3, then MPLL_MULTPLIER, REF_CLK_DIV2, and SSC_REF_CLK_SEL
05975                                                          must all be programmed to the same frequency setting. */
05976     uint64_t ref_clk_fsel                 : 6;  /**< Selects the reference clock frequency for the SuperSpeed and high-speed PLL blocks.
05977                                                          The legal values are:
05978                                                            If REF_CLK_SEL = 0x0 or 0x1, then:
05979                                                              0x27 = 100  MHz on DLMC_REF_CLK*
05980                                                            If REF_CLK_SEL = 0x2 or 0x3, then:
05981                                                              0x07 is the only legal value.
05982                                                          All other values are reserved.
05983                                                          This value may only be changed during [UPHY_RST].
05984                                                          Note: When REF_CLK_SEL = 0x2 or 0x3, the MPLL_MULTIPLIER, REF_CLK_DIV2, and
05985                                                          SSC_REF_CLK_SEL settings are used to configure the SuperSpeed reference clock
05986                                                          multiplier. */
05987     uint64_t reserved_31_31               : 1;
05988     uint64_t h_clk_en                     : 1;  /**< Controller-clock enable. When set to 1, the controller clock is generated. This also
05989                                                          enables access to UCTL registers 0x30-0xF8. */
05990     uint64_t h_clk_byp_sel                : 1;  /**< Select the bypass input to the controller-clock divider.
05991                                                          0 = Use the divided coprocessor clock from the H_CLKDIV divider.
05992                                                          1 = Use the bypass clock from the GPIO pins.
05993                                                          This signal is just a multiplexer-select signal; it does not enable the controller clock.
05994                                                          You must still set H_CLK_EN separately. H_CLK_BYP_SEL select should not be changed
05995                                                          unless H_CLK_EN is disabled.
05996                                                          The bypass clock can be selected and running even if the controller-clock dividers are not
05997                                                          running. */
05998     uint64_t h_clkdiv_rst                 : 1;  /**< Controller clock divider reset. Divided clocks are not generated while the divider is
05999                                                          being reset.
06000                                                          This also resets the suspend-clock divider. */
06001     uint64_t reserved_27_27               : 1;
06002     uint64_t h_clkdiv_sel                 : 3;  /**< Controller clock-frequency-divider select. The controller-clock frequency is the
06003                                                          coprocessor-clock frequency divided by [H_CLKDIV_SEL] and must be at or below 300 MHz.
06004                                                          The divider values are the following:
06005                                                          0x0 = divide by 1.
06006                                                          0x1 = divide by 2.
06007                                                          0x2 = divide by 4.
06008                                                          0x3 = divide by 6.
06009                                                          0x4 = divide by 8.
06010                                                          0x5 = divide by 16.
06011                                                          0x6 = divide by 24.
06012                                                          0x7 = divide by 32.
06013                                                          The hclk frequency must be at or below 300 MHz.
06014                                                          The hclk frequency must be at or above 150 MHz for full-rate USB3
06015                                                          operation.
06016                                                          The hclk frequency must be at or above 125 MHz for any USB3
06017                                                          functionality.
06018                                                          If [DRD_MODE] = DEVICE, the hclk frequency must be at or above 125 MHz for
06019                                                          correct USB2 functionality.
06020                                                          If [DRD_MODE] = HOST, the hclk frequency must be at or above 90 MHz
06021                                                          for full-rate USB2 operation.
06022                                                          If [DRD_MODE] = HOST, the hclk frequency must be at or above 62.5 MHz
06023                                                          for any USB2 operation.
06024                                                          This field can be changed only when [H_CLKDIV_RST] = 1. */
06025     uint64_t reserved_22_23               : 2;
06026     uint64_t usb3_port_perm_attach        : 1;  /**< Indicates this port is permanently attached. This is a strap signal; it should be modified
06027                                                          only when [UPHY_RST] is asserted. */
06028     uint64_t usb2_port_perm_attach        : 1;  /**< Indicates this port is permanently attached. This is a strap signal; it should be modified
06029                                                          only when [UPHY_RST] is asserted. */
06030     uint64_t reserved_19_19               : 1;
06031     uint64_t usb3_port_disable            : 1;  /**< Disables the USB3 (SuperSpeed) portion of this PHY. When set to 1, this signal stops
06032                                                          reporting connect/disconnect events on the port and keeps the port in disabled state. This
06033                                                          could be used for security reasons where hardware can disable a port regardless of whether
06034                                                          xHCI driver enables a port or not.
06035                                                          USBDRD()_UAHC_HCSPARAMS1[MAXPORTS] is not affected by this signal.
06036                                                          This is a strap signal; it should be modified only when [UPHY_RST] is asserted. */
06037     uint64_t reserved_17_17               : 1;
06038     uint64_t usb2_port_disable            : 1;  /**< Disables USB2 (high-speed/full-speed/low-speed) portion of this PHY. When set to 1, this
06039                                                          signal stops reporting connect/disconnect events on the port and keeps the port in
06040                                                          disabled state. This could be used for security reasons where hardware can disable a port
06041                                                          regardless of whether xHCI driver enables a port or not.
06042                                                          USBDRD()_UAHC_HCSPARAMS1[MAXPORTS] is not affected by this signal.
06043                                                          This is a strap signal; it should only be modified when [UPHY_RST] is asserted.
06044                                                          If Port0 is required to be disabled, ensure that the utmi_clk[0] is running at the normal
06045                                                          speed. Also, all the enabled USB2.0 ports should have the same clock frequency as Port0. */
06046     uint64_t reserved_15_15               : 1;
06047     uint64_t ss_power_en                  : 1;  /**< PHY SuperSpeed block power enable.
06048                                                          This is a strap signal; it should only be modified when [UPHY_RST] is asserted. */
06049     uint64_t reserved_13_13               : 1;
06050     uint64_t hs_power_en                  : 1;  /**< PHY high-speed block power enable.
06051                                                          This is a strap signal; it should only be modified when [UPHY_RST] is asserted. */
06052     uint64_t reserved_5_11                : 7;
06053     uint64_t csclk_en                     : 1;  /**< Turns on the USB UCTL interface clock (coprocessor clock). This enables access to UAHC
06054                                                          registers via the IOI, as well as UCTL registers starting from 0x30 via the RSL bus. */
06055     uint64_t drd_mode                     : 1;  /**< Switches between host or device mode for USBDRD.
06056                                                          1 - Device
06057                                                          0 - Host */
06058     uint64_t uphy_rst                     : 1;  /**< PHY reset; resets UPHY; active-high. */
06059     uint64_t uahc_rst                     : 1;  /**< Software reset; resets UAHC; active-high. */
06060     uint64_t uctl_rst                     : 1;  /**< Software reset; resets UCTL; active-high.
06061                                                          Resets UAHC DMA and register shims. Resets UCTL RSL registers 0x30-0xF8.
06062                                                          Does not reset UCTL RSL registers 0x0-0x28.
06063                                                          UCTL RSL registers starting from 0x30 can be accessed only after the controller clock is
06064                                                          active and [UCTL_RST] is deasserted. */
06065 #else
06066     uint64_t uctl_rst                     : 1;
06067     uint64_t uahc_rst                     : 1;
06068     uint64_t uphy_rst                     : 1;
06069     uint64_t drd_mode                     : 1;
06070     uint64_t csclk_en                     : 1;
06071     uint64_t reserved_5_11                : 7;
06072     uint64_t hs_power_en                  : 1;
06073     uint64_t reserved_13_13               : 1;
06074     uint64_t ss_power_en                  : 1;
06075     uint64_t reserved_15_15               : 1;
06076     uint64_t usb2_port_disable            : 1;
06077     uint64_t reserved_17_17               : 1;
06078     uint64_t usb3_port_disable            : 1;
06079     uint64_t reserved_19_19               : 1;
06080     uint64_t usb2_port_perm_attach        : 1;
06081     uint64_t usb3_port_perm_attach        : 1;
06082     uint64_t reserved_22_23               : 2;
06083     uint64_t h_clkdiv_sel                 : 3;
06084     uint64_t reserved_27_27               : 1;
06085     uint64_t h_clkdiv_rst                 : 1;
06086     uint64_t h_clk_byp_sel                : 1;
06087     uint64_t h_clk_en                     : 1;
06088     uint64_t reserved_31_31               : 1;
06089     uint64_t ref_clk_fsel                 : 6;
06090     uint64_t ref_clk_div2                 : 1;
06091     uint64_t ref_ssp_en                   : 1;
06092     uint64_t mpll_multiplier              : 7;
06093     uint64_t ssc_ref_clk_sel              : 9;
06094     uint64_t ssc_range                    : 3;
06095     uint64_t ssc_en                       : 1;
06096     uint64_t ref_clk_sel                  : 2;
06097     uint64_t start_bist                   : 1;
06098     uint64_t clear_bist                   : 1;
06099 #endif
06100     } s;
06101     struct cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_ctl_s        cn70xx;
06102     struct cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_ctl_s        cn70xxp1;
06103     struct cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_ctl_s        cn73xx;
06104     struct cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_ctl_s        cnf75xx;
06105 };

06108 /**
06109  * cvmx_usbdrd#_uctl_ecc
06110  *
06111  * This register can be used to disable ECC correction, insert ECC errors, and debug ECC
06112  * failures.
06113  * * The ECC_ERR* fields are captured when there are no outstanding ECC errors indicated in
06114  * INTSTAT and a new ECC error arrives. Prioritization for multiple events occurring on the same
06115  * cycle is indicated by the ECC_ERR_SOURCE enumeration: highest encoded value has highest
06116  * priority.
06117  * * The *ECC_*_DIS fields disable ECC correction; SBE and DBE errors are still reported. If
06118  * *ECC_*_DIS = 0x1, then no data-correction occurs.
06119  * * The *ECC_FLIP_SYND fields flip the syndrome<1:0> bits to generate single-bit/double-bit
06120  * error for testing.
06121  *
06122  * 0x0 = Normal operation.
06123  * 0x1 = SBE on bit[0].
06124  * 0x2 = SBE on bit[1].
06125  * 0x3 = DBE on bit[1:0].
06126  *
06127  * This register is accessible only when USBDRD()_UCTL_CTL[H_CLK_EN] = 1.
06128  *
06129  * This register can be reset by IOI reset or with USBDRD()_UCTL_CTL[UCTL_RST].
06130  */
06131 union cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_ecc {
06132     uint64_t u64;
06133     struct cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_ecc_s {
06134 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
06135     uint64_t reserved_60_63               : 4;

06137     uint64_t ecc_err_syndrome             : 8;  /**< Syndrome bits of the ECC error. */
06138     uint64_t ecc_err_address              : 16; /**< RAM address of the ECC error. */
06139     uint64_t reserved_21_31               : 11;
06140     uint64_t uctl_xm_r_ecc_flip_synd      : 2;  /**< Insert ECC error for testing purposes. */
06141     uint64_t uctl_xm_r_ecc_cor_dis        : 1;  /**< Enables ECC correction on UCTL AxiMaster read-data FIFO. */
06142     uint64_t uctl_xm_w_ecc_flip_synd      : 2;  /**< Insert ECC error for testing purposes. */
06143     uint64_t uctl_xm_w_ecc_cor_dis        : 1;  /**< Enables ECC correction on UCTL AxiMaster write-data FIFO. */
06144     uint64_t reserved_9_14                : 6;
06145     uint64_t uahc_ram2_ecc_flip_synd      : 2;  /**< Insert ECC error for testing purposes. */

06151 #else
06152     uint64_t uahc_ram0_ecc_cor_dis        : 1;

06157     uint64_t uahc_ram2_ecc_flip_synd      : 2;
06158     uint64_t reserved_9_14                : 6;
06159     uint64_t uctl_xm_w_ecc_cor_dis        : 1;
06160     uint64_t uctl_xm_w_ecc_flip_synd      : 2;
06161     uint64_t uctl_xm_r_ecc_cor_dis        : 1;
06162     uint64_t uctl_xm_r_ecc_flip_synd      : 2;
06163     uint64_t reserved_21_31               : 11;
06164     uint64_t ecc_err_address              : 16;
06165     uint64_t ecc_err_syndrome             : 8;
06166     uint64_t ecc_err_source               : 4;
06167     uint64_t reserved_60_63               : 4;
06168 #endif
06169     } s;

06203 /**
06204  * cvmx_usbdrd#_uctl_host_cfg
06205  *
06206  * This register allows configuration of various host controller (UAHC) features. Most of these
06207  * are strap signals and should be modified only while the controller is not running.
06208  *
06209  * This register is accessible only when USBDRD()_UCTL_CTL[H_CLK_EN] = 1.
06210  *
06211  * This register can be reset by IOI reset or with USBDRD()_UCTL_CTL[UCTL_RST].
06212  */
06213 union cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_host_cfg {
06214     uint64_t u64;
06215     struct cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_host_cfg_s {
06216 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
06217     uint64_t reserved_60_63               : 4;
06218     uint64_t host_current_belt            : 12; /**< This signal indicates the minimum value of all received BELT values and the BELT that is
06219                                                          set by the Set LTV command. */
06220     uint64_t reserved_38_47               : 10;
06221     uint64_t fla                          : 6;  /**< High-speed jitter adjustment. Indicates the correction required to accommodate mac3 clock
06222                                                          and utmi clock jitter to measure 125us duration. With FLA tied to 0x0, the high-speed
06223                                                          125us micro-frame is counted for 123933ns. The value needs to be programmed in terms of
06224                                                          high-speed bit times in a 30 MHz cycle. Default value that needs to be driven is 0x20
06225                                                          (assuming 30 MHz perfect clock).
06226                                                          FLA connects to the FLADJ register defined in the xHCI spec in the PCI configuration
06227                                                          space. Each count is equal to 16 high-speed bit times. By default when this register is
06228                                                          set to 0x20, it gives 125us interval. Now, based on the clock accuracy, you can decrement
06229                                                          the count or increment the count to get the 125 us uSOF window.
06230                                                          This is a strap signal; it should only be modified when UAHC is in reset (soft-reset
06231                                                          okay). */
06232     uint64_t reserved_29_31               : 3;
06233     uint64_t bme                          : 1;  /**< Bus-master enable. This signal is used to disable the bus-mastering capability of the
06234                                                          host. Disabling this capability stalls DMA accesses. */
06235     uint64_t oci_en                       : 1;  /**< Overcurrent-indication enable. When enabled, OCI input to UAHC is taken from the GPIO
06236                                                          signals and sense-converted based on OCI_ACTIVE_HIGH_EN. The MIO GPIO multiplexer must be
06237                                                          programmed accordingly.
06238                                                          When disabled, OCI input to UAHC is forced to the correct inactive state based on
06239                                                          OCI_ACTIVE_HIGH_EN.
06240                                                          This is a strap signal; it should only be modified when UAHC is in reset (soft-reset
06241                                                          okay). */
06242     uint64_t oci_active_high_en           : 1;  /**< Overcurrent sense selection. The off-chip sense (high/low) is converted to match the
06243                                                          controller's active-high sense.
06244                                                          0 = Overcurrent indication from off-chip source is active-low.
06245                                                          1 = Overcurrent indication from off-chip source is active-high.
06246                                                          This is a strap signal; it should only be modified when UAHC is in reset (soft-reset
06247                                                          okay). */
06248     uint64_t ppc_en                       : 1;  /**< Port-power-control enable.
06249                                                          0 = USBDRD()_UAHC_HCCPARAMS[PPC] report port-power-control feature is unavailable.
06250                                                          1 = USBDRD()_UAHC_HCCPARAMS[PPC] reports port-power-control feature is available. PPC
06251                                                          output
06252                                                          from UAHC is taken to the GPIO signals and sense-converted based on PPC_ACTIVE_HIGH_EN.
06253                                                          The MIO GPIO multiplexer must be programmed accordingly.
06254                                                          This is a strap signal; it should only be modified when either the UCTL_CTL[UAHC] or
06255                                                          UAHC_GCTL[CORESOFTRESET] is asserted. */
06256     uint64_t ppc_active_high_en           : 1;  /**< Port power control sense selection. The active-high port-power-control output to off-chip
06257                                                          source is converted to match the off-chip sense.
06258                                                          0 = Port-power control to off-chip source is active-low.
06259                                                          1 = Port-power control to off-chip source is active-high.
06260                                                          This is a strap signal; it should only be modified when either the UCTL_CTL[UAHC] or
06261                                                          UAHC_GCTL[CORESOFTRESET] is asserted. */
06262     uint64_t reserved_0_23                : 24;
06263 #else
06264     uint64_t reserved_0_23                : 24;
06265     uint64_t ppc_active_high_en           : 1;
06266     uint64_t ppc_en                       : 1;
06267     uint64_t oci_active_high_en           : 1;
06268     uint64_t oci_en                       : 1;
06269     uint64_t bme                          : 1;
06270     uint64_t reserved_29_31               : 3;
06271     uint64_t fla                          : 6;
06272     uint64_t reserved_38_47               : 10;
06273     uint64_t host_current_belt            : 12;
06274     uint64_t reserved_60_63               : 4;
06275 #endif
06276     } s;

06383 /**
06384  * cvmx_usbdrd#_uctl_port#_cfg_hs
06385  *
06386  * This register controls configuration and test controls for the high-speed port 0 PHY.
06387  *
06388  * This register is accessible only when USBDRD()_UCTL_CTL[H_CLK_EN] = 1.
06389  *
06390  * This register can be reset by IOI reset or with USBDRD()_UCTL_CTL[UCTL_RST].
06391  */
06392 union cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_portx_cfg_hs {
06393     uint64_t u64;
06394     struct cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_portx_cfg_hs_s {
06395 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
06396     uint64_t reserved_58_63               : 6;
06397     uint64_t comp_dis_tune                : 3;  /**< Disconnect threshold voltage. Adjusts the voltage level for the threshold used to detect a
06398                                                          disconnect event at the host.
06399                                                          A positive binary bit setting change results in a +1.5% incremental change in the
06400                                                          threshold voltage level, while a negative binary bit setting change results in a -1.5%
06401                                                          incremental change in the threshold voltage level. */
06402     uint64_t sq_rx_tune                   : 3;  /**< Squelch threshold adjustment. Adjusts the voltage level for the threshold used to detect
06403                                                          valid high-speed data.
06404                                                          A positive binary bit setting change results in a -5% incremental change in threshold
06405                                                          voltage level, while a negative binary bit setting change results in a +5% incremental
06406                                                          change in threshold voltage level. */
06407     uint64_t tx_fsls_tune                 : 4;  /**< Low-speed/full-speed source impedance adjustment. Adjusts the low- and full-speed single-
06408                                                          ended source impedance while driving high. This parameter control is encoded in
06409                                                          thermometer code.
06410                                                          A positive thermometer code change results in a -2.5% incremental change in source
06411                                                          impedance. A negative thermometer code change results in +2.5% incremental change in
06412                                                          source impedance. Any non-thermometer code setting (that is, 0x9) is not supported and
06413                                                          reserved. */
06414     uint64_t reserved_46_47               : 2;
06415     uint64_t tx_hs_xv_tune                : 2;  /**< Transmitter high-speed crossover adjustment. This bus adjusts the voltage at which the DP0
06416                                                          and DM0 signals cross while transmitting in high-speed mode.
06417                                                          0x0 = reserved.
06418                                                          0x1 = -15 mV.
06419                                                          0x2 = +15 mV.
06420                                                          0x3 = default setting. */
06421     uint64_t tx_preemp_amp_tune           : 2;  /**< High-speed transmitter preemphasis current control. Controls the amount of current
06422                                                          sourced to DP0 and DM0 after a J-to-K or K-to-J transition. The high-speed transmitter
06423                                                          preemphasis current is defined in terms of unit amounts. One unit amount is approximately
06424                                                          600 A and is defined as 1* preemphasis current.
06425                                                          0x0 = High-speed TX preemphasis is disabled.
06426                                                          0x1 = High-speed TX preemphasis circuit sources 1* preemphasis current.
06427                                                          0x2 = High-speed TX preemphasis circuit sources 2* preemphasis current.
06428                                                          0x3 = High-speed TX preemphasis circuit sources 3* preemphasis current.
06429                                                          If these signals are not used, set them to 0x0. */
06430     uint64_t reserved_41_41               : 1;
06431     uint64_t tx_preemp_pulse_tune         : 1;  /**< High-speed transmitter preemphasis duration control. Controls the duration for which the
06432                                                          high-speed preemphasis current is sourced onto DP0 or DM0. The high-speed transmitter
06433                                                          preemphasis duration is defined in terms of unit amounts. One unit of preemphasis duration
06434                                                          is approximately 580 ps and is defined as 1* preemphasis duration. This signal is valid
06435                                                          only if either TX_PREEMP_AMP_TUNE0[1] or TX_PREEMP_AMP_TUNE0[0] is set to 1.
06436                                                          0 = 2*, long preemphasis current duration (design default)
06437                                                          1 = 1*, short preemphasis current duration
06438                                                          If this signal is not used, set it to 0. */
06439     uint64_t tx_res_tune                  : 2;  /**< USB source-impedance adjustment. Some applications require additional devices to be added
06440                                                          on the USB, such as a series switch, which can add significant series resistance. This bus
06441                                                          adjusts the driver source impedance to compensate for added series resistance on the USB.
06442                                                          0x0 = source impedance is decreased by approximately 1.5 ohm.
06443                                                          0x1 = design default.
06444                                                          0x2 = source impedance is decreased by approximately 2 ohm.
06445                                                          0x3 = source impedance is decreased by approximately 4 ohm.
06446                                                          Any setting other than the default can result in source-impedance variation across
06447                                                          process, voltage, and temperature conditions that does not meet USB 2.0 specification
06448                                                          limits. If this bus is not used, leave it at the default setting. */
06449     uint64_t tx_rise_tune                 : 2;  /**< High-speed transmitter rise-/fall-time adjustment. Adjusts the rise/fall times of the
06450                                                          high-speed waveform. A positive binary bit setting change results in a -4% incremental
06451                                                          change in the high-speed rise/fall time. A negative binary bit setting change results in a
06452                                                          +4% incremental change in the high-speed rise/fall time. */
06453     uint64_t tx_vref_tune                 : 4;  /**< High-speed DC voltage-level adjustment. Adjusts the high-speed DC level voltage.
06454                                                          A positive binary-bit-setting change results in a +1.25% incremental change in high-speed
06455                                                          DC voltage level, while a negative binary-bit-setting change results in a -1.25%
06456                                                          incremental change in high-speed DC voltage level.
06457                                                          The default bit setting is intended to create a HighSpeed transmit
06458                                                          DC level of approximately 400mV. */
06459     uint64_t reserved_7_31                : 25;
06460     uint64_t otgtune                      : 3;  /**< "VBUS Valid Threshold Adjustment
06461                                                          Function: This bus adjusts the voltage level for the VBUS<\#>
06462                                                          valid threshold. To enable tuning at the board level, connect this
06463                                                          bus to a register.
06464                                                          Note: A positive binary bit setting change results in a +3%
06465                                                          incremental change in threshold voltage level, while a negative
06466                                                          binary bit setting change results in a -3% incremental change
06467                                                          in threshold voltage level. " */
06468     uint64_t vatest_enable                : 2;  /**< Analog test-pin select. Enables analog test voltages to be placed on the ID0 pin.
06469                                                          0x0 = Test functionality disabled.
06470                                                          0x1 = Test functionality enabled.
06471                                                          0x2, 0x3 = Reserved, invalid settings.
06472                                                          See also the PHY databook for details on how to select which analog test voltage. */
06473     uint64_t loopback_enable              : 1;  /**< Places the high-speed PHY in loopback mode, which concurrently enables high-speed receive
06474                                                          and transmit logic. */
06475     uint64_t atereset                     : 1;  /**< Per-PHY ATE reset. When the USB core is powered up (not in suspend mode), an automatic
06476                                                          tester can use this to disable PHYCLOCK and FREECLK, then re-enable them with an aligned
06477                                                          phase.
06478                                                          0 = PHYCLOCK and FREECLK are available within a specific period after ATERESET is
06479                                                          deasserted.
06480                                                          1 = PHYCLOCK and FREECLK outputs are disabled. */
06481 #else
06482     uint64_t atereset                     : 1;
06483     uint64_t loopback_enable              : 1;
06484     uint64_t vatest_enable                : 2;
06485     uint64_t otgtune                      : 3;

06487     uint64_t tx_vref_tune                 : 4;
06488     uint64_t tx_rise_tune                 : 2;
06489     uint64_t tx_res_tune                  : 2;
06490     uint64_t tx_preemp_pulse_tune         : 1;
06491     uint64_t reserved_41_41               : 1;
06492     uint64_t tx_preemp_amp_tune           : 2;
06493     uint64_t tx_hs_xv_tune                : 2;
06494     uint64_t reserved_46_47               : 2;
06495     uint64_t tx_fsls_tune                 : 4;

06497     uint64_t comp_dis_tune                : 3;

06508 /**
06509  * cvmx_usbdrd#_uctl_port#_cfg_ss
06510  *
06511  * This register controls configuration and test controls for the SS port 0 PHY.
06512  *
06513  * This register is accessible only when USBDRD()_UCTL_CTL[H_CLK_EN] = 1.
06514  *
06515  * This register can be reset by IOI reset or with USBDRD()_UCTL_CTL[UCTL_RST].
06516  */
06517 union cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_portx_cfg_ss {
06518     uint64_t u64;
06519     struct cvmx_usbdrdx_uctl_portx_cfg_ss_s {
06520 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
06521     uint64_t tx_vboost_lvl                : 3;  /**< TX voltage-boost level. Sets the boosted transmit launch amplitude (mVppd). The default
06522                                                          bit setting is intended to set the launch amplitude to approximately 1,008 mVppd. A
06523                                                          single, positive binary bit setting change results in a +156 mVppd change in the TX launch
06524                                                          amplitude.
06525                                                          A single, negative binary bit setting change results in a -156 mVppd change in the TX
06526                                                          launch amplitude. All settings more than one binary bit change should not be used.
06527                                                          0x3 = 0.844 V launch amplitude.
06528                                                          0x4 = 1.008 V launch amplitude.
06529                                                          0x5 = 1.156 V launch amplitude.
06530                                                          All others values are invalid. */
06531     uint64_t los_bias                     : 3;  /**< Loss-of-signal detector threshold-level control. A positive, binary bit setting change
06532                                                          results in a +15 mVp incremental change in the LOS threshold.
06533                                                          A negative binary bit setting change results in a -15 mVp incremental change in the LOS
06534                                                          threshold. The 0x0 setting is reserved and must not be used. The default 0x5 setting
06535                                                          corresponds to approximately 105 mVp.
06536                                                          0x0 = invalid.
06537                                                          0x1 = 45 mV.
06538                                                          0x2 = 60 mV.
06539                                                          0x3 = 75 mV.
06540                                                          0x4 = 90 mV.
06541                                                          0x5 = 105 mV (default).
06542                                                          0x6 = 120 mV.
06543                                                          0x7 = 135 mV. */
06544     uint64_t lane0_ext_pclk_req           : 1;  /**< When asserted, this signal enables the pipe0_pclk output regardless of power state (along
06545                                                          with the associated increase in power consumption). You can use this input to enable
06546                                                          pipe0_pclk in the P3 state without going through a complete boot sequence. */
06547     uint64_t lane0_tx2rx_loopbk           : 1;  /**< When asserted, data from TX predriver is looped back to RX slicers. LOS is bypassed and
06548                                                          based on the tx0_en input so that rx0_los = !tx_data_en. */
06549     uint64_t reserved_42_55               : 14;
06550     uint64_t pcs_rx_los_mask_val          : 10; /**< Configurable loss-of-signal mask width. Sets the number of reference clock cycles to mask
06551                                                          the incoming LFPS in U3 and U2 states. Masks the incoming LFPS for the number of reference
06552                                                          clock cycles equal to the value of pcs_rx_los_mask_val<9:0>. This control filters out
06553                                                          short, non-compliant LFPS glitches sent by a noncompliant host.
06554                                                          For normal operation, set to a targeted mask interval of 10us (value = 10us / Tref_clk).
06555                                                          If the USBDRD()_UCTL_CTL[REF_CLK_DIV2] is used, then
06556                                                          (value = 10us / (2 * Tref_clk)). These equations are based on the SuperSpeed reference
06557                                                          clock frequency. The value of PCS_RX_LOS_MASK_VAL should be as follows:
06558                                                          <pre>
06559                                                               Frequency   DIV2  LOS_MASK
06560                                                               ---------    ---  --------
06561                                                               200   MHz      1     0x3E8
06562                                                               125   MHz      0     0x4E2
06563                                                               104   MHz      0     0x410
06564                                                               100   MHz      0     0x3E8
06565                                                                96   MHz      0     0x3C0
06566                                                                76.8 MHz      1     0x180
06567                                                                52   MHz      0     0x208
06568                                                                50   MHz      0     0x1F4
06569                                                                48   MHz      0     0x1E0
06570                                                                40   MHz      1     0x0C8
06571                                                                38.4 MHz      0     0x180
06572                                                                26   MHz      0     0x104
06573                                                                25   MHz      0     0x0FA
06574                                                                24   MHz      0     0x0F0
06575                                                                20   MHz      0     0x0C8
06576                                                                19.2 MHz      0     0x0C0
06577                                                          </pre>
06578                                                          Setting this bus to 0x0 disables masking. The value should be defined when the PHY is in
06579                                                          reset. Changing this value during operation might disrupt normal operation of the link. */
06580     uint64_t pcs_tx_deemph_3p5db          : 6;  /**< Fine-tune transmitter driver deemphasis when set to 3.5db.
06581                                                          This static value sets the TX driver deemphasis value when
06582                                                          USBDRD()_UAHC_GUSB3PIPECTL()[TXDEEMPHASIS] is set to
06583                                                          0x1 (according to the PIPE3 specification). The values for transmit deemphasis are derived
06584                                                          from the following equation:
06585                                                          _ TX deemphasis (db) = 20 * log_base_10((128 - 2 * pcs_tx_deemph)/128)
06586                                                          In general, the parameter controls are static signals to be set prior to taking the PHY
06587                                                          out of reset. However, you can dynamically change these values on-the-fly for test
06588                                                          purposes. In this case, changes to the transmitter to reflect the current value occur only
06589                                                          after USBDRD()_UAHC_GUSB3PIPECTL()[TXDEEMPHASIS] changes. */
06590     uint64_t pcs_tx_deemph_6db            : 6;  /**< Fine-tune transmitter driver deemphasis when set to 6 db.
06591                                                          This static value sets the TX driver deemphasis value when
06592                                                          USBDRD()_UAHC_GUSB3PIPECTL()[TXDEEMPHASIS]  is set to
06593                                                          0x0 (according to the PIPE3 specification). This bus is provided for completeness and as a
06594                                                          second potential launch amplitude. The values for transmit deemphasis are derived from the
06595                                                          following equation:
06596                                                          _ TX deemphasis (db) = 20 * log_base_10((128 - 2 * pcs_tx_deemph)/128)
06597                                                          In general, the parameter controls are static signals to be set prior to taking the PHY
06598                                                          out of reset. However, you can dynamically change these values on-the-fly for test
06599                                                          purposes. In this case, changes to the transmitter to reflect the current value occur only
06600                                                          after USBDRD()_UAHC_GUSB3PIPECTL()[TXDEEMPHASIS] changes. */
06601     uint64_t pcs_tx_swing_full            : 7;  /**< Launch amplitude of the transmitter. Sets the launch amplitude of the transmitter. The
06602                                                          values for transmit amplitude are derived from the following equation:
06603                                                          TX amplitude (V) = vptx * ((pcs_tx_swing_full + 1)/128)
06604                                                          In general, the parameter controls are static signals to be set prior to taking the PHY
06605                                                          out of reset. However, you can dynamically change these values on-the-fly for test
06606                                                          purposes. In this case, changes to the transmitter to reflect the current value occur only
06607                                                          after USBDRD()_UAHC_GUSB3PIPECTL()[TXDEEMPHASIS] changes. */
06608     uint64_t lane0_tx_term_offset         : 5;  /**< Transmitter termination offset. Reserved, set to 0x0. */
06609     uint64_t reserved_6_7                 : 2;
06610     uint64_t res_tune_ack                 : 1;  /**< Resistor tune acknowledge. While asserted, indicates a resistor tune is in progress. */
06611     uint64_t res_tune_req                 : 1;  /**< Resistor tune request. The rising edge triggers a resistor tune request (if one is not
06612                                                          already in progress). When asserted, [RES_TUNE_ACK] is asserted high until calibration of
06613                                                          the termination impedance is complete.
06614                                                          Tuning disrupts the normal flow of data; therefore, assert [RES_TUNE_REQ] only when the
06615                                                          PHY
06616                                                          is inactive. The PHY automatically performs a tune when coming out of PRST. */
06617     uint64_t reserved_0_3                 : 4;
06618 #else
06619     uint64_t reserved_0_3                 : 4;
06620     uint64_t res_tune_req                 : 1;
06621     uint64_t res_tune_ack                 : 1;
06622     uint64_t reserved_6_7                 : 2;
06623     uint64_t lane0_tx_term_offset         : 5;
06624     uint64_t pcs_tx_swing_full            : 7;
06625     uint64_t pcs_tx_deemph_6db            : 6;
06626     uint64_t pcs_tx_deemph_3p5db          : 6;
06627     uint64_t pcs_rx_los_mask_val          : 10;
06628     uint64_t reserved_42_55               : 14;
06629     uint64_t lane0_tx2rx_loopbk           : 1;
06630     uint64_t lane0_ext_pclk_req           : 1;

06633 #endif
06634     } s;
